  , issueCommentBody =
      "You can use `r.args` for this.\r\n\r\nSomething like this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.table('users').getAll(r.args(r.table('comments')('user').coerceTo('array')))\r\n```\r\n\r\nBe careful when your `obj('projects')` is an empty array, as `.getAll()` does not currently support empty queries -- it will return the (misleading) error `Expected 2 or more argument(s) but found 1` when you try to do something like `r.table('projects').getAll(r.args([]))`\r\n\r\nAs a workaround, you can use `r.branch` as described in #2586 or something a bit trickier like: \r\n\r\n```js\r\nr.table('users').getAll(r.args(r.table('comments')('user').coerceTo('array').append('does-not-exist')))\r\n```\r\n\r\n#2463 exists to track the misleading error message.\r\n\r\n#2588 exists to track `getAll` taking zero arguments."
  , issueCommentId = 51939736
